    <!-- Chosen Palette: Calm & Authoritative -->
    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The application is structured as a narrative-driven, single-page dashboard. It starts with high-impact, aggregate numbers (KPIs) to immediately establish the scale of the pilot's career. It then flows into more detailed, comparative visualizations (Experience Breakdown) allowing users to understand the composition of his flight hours. This is followed by a clear, organized list of his technical qualifications (Aircraft Expertise) and a chronological view of his career progression (Career Timeline). This thematic, top-down structure was chosen over a direct resume format to guide the user from a broad overview to specific details, enhancing comprehension and creating a more engaging user journey. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - Total/PIC Hours -> Goal: Inform -> Viz: Dynamic Stats (Big Numbers) -> Interaction: None -> Justification: Provides immediate, high-impact understanding of career scope. Method: Styled HTML. (CONFIRM: NO SVG).
        - PIC vs Total Hours -> Goal: Compare -> Viz: Donut Chart -> Interaction: Hover Tooltip -> Justification: Best for showing a clear part-to-whole relationship of command time. Library: Chart.js (Canvas). (CONFIRM: NO SVG).
        - PIC Hours by Type -> Goal: Compare -> Viz: Bar Chart -> Interaction: Hover Tooltip -> Justification: Ideal for comparing distinct categories of flight experience. Library: Chart.js (Canvas). (CONFIRM: NO SVG).
        - Career History -> Goal: Change -> Viz: Timeline -> Interaction: Scroll -> Justification: Visually represents career progression chronologically, which is more intuitive than a table. Method: Structured HTML/CSS. (CONFIRM: NO SVG/Mermaid).
        - Aircraft Flown -> Goal: Organize -> Viz: Styled Grid -> Interaction: None -> Justification: A clean, scannable format to display a wide range of qualifications. Method: Styled HTML with Unicode. (CONFIRM: NO SVG).
    -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
